y-month voyage covered more than eight thousand miles."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Indian Rocks Beach bridge tender for 25 years","body":"After his sailing journey he returned in 1910 to Indian Rocks Beach Florida — a stop remembered from the Gazelle voyage. He served as bridge tender at the wooden bridge there for twenty-five years until his 1933 retirement, living in a small cabin midway across the bridge where 'kids went to Cap on the bridge with their troubles and their broken toys.'"},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"Raised American flag every day after Pearl Harbor","body":"After Pearl Harbor he raised the American flag over the Indian Rocks Beach bridge every day — 'buying new ones from his own pocket money as they wore out.' The daily flag-raising continued through his later retirement years."},{"number":4,"category":"legacy","header":"Doubleday published 'A Year on a Yawl'","body":"American Boy magazine editor W C Sprague persuaded him to write his sailing experience as an eighteen-month serial. Doubleday Page & Co published the result as 'A Year on a Yawl,' which also ran as a serial in seven newspapers."}],"slug":"kenneth-ransom-1876"},"HD2826":{"id":"HD2826","has_descendants_documented":false,"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1866,"month":1,"day":1},"death":{"year":1893,"month":1,"day":1},"parents":{"father_id":"HD2683","mother_id":"X00913"},"marriages":[],"tags":[],"sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"William C. Ransom","first_name":"William","middle_name":"C.","last_name":"Ransom","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":